The following table summarizes the integrated functionality of the sub‑systems, demonstrating how the leg operates as a closed thermodynamic system.

Sub‑System Primary Function Secondary "Hidden" Benefit
Polycentric Knee (CAFP) Shifts ICR for maximum torque at $15^\circ$ flexion. Protects SPEA from impact via geometry; dust‑proof flexures eliminate friction losses.
Biarticular Tendon Recycles energy from knee to ankle during push‑off. Powers the Foot Jamming Mechanism and eliminates swing‑phase slack.
Mechanical Piston (MCJF) Stabilizes foot in regolith by jamming granular media. Acts as a secondary impact dampener for landing; load‑proportional stiffening.
